virtual bool sxsdk::exporter_interface::can_accept_link ( void *  aux = 0  )  [inline, virtual]

Overridable. Override and return true if the plugin can handle link objects.

If false is returned, make the link objects real objects and call the callback functions like do_sphere() and do_polygon().

virtual bool sxsdk::exporter_interface::can_accept_meshes ( void *  aux = 0  )  [inline, virtual]

Overridable. If override and return false, the plugins avoid calling do_meshes to process by polygonmesh.

Call do_meshes if true is returned.

virtual int sxsdk::exporter_interface::get_max_vertices_per_face ( void *  aux = 0  )  [inline, virtual]

Overridable. Override and return the maximum number of vertices per polygon mesh face that the plugin can handle. 3, 4 and -1 are valid, and -1 means no limit.

virtual bool sxsdk::exporter_interface::must_triangulate_polymesh ( void *  aux = 0  )  [inline, virtual]

Overridable. Faces of polygon mesh objects will be triangulated if this function returns true.

If false is returned, the polygon will be divided into the number of vertices set with get_max_vertices_per_face().

virtual void sxsdk::exporter_interface::polymesh_face_uv ( int  n_list,
const int  list[],
const sxsdk::vec3 *  normals,
const sxsdk::vec4 *  plane_equation,
const sxsdk::vec2 *  uvs,
void *  aux = 0 
) [inline, virtual]

Overridable. Infomation on a polygon mesh face along with its vertices uv parameters are passed to the plugin.

Only the parameter's UV values are passed. If the UV values are not needed, use polymesh_face(). If distance correction UV values are needed, use polymesh_face_uvuv() or polymesh_face_uvs() .

Parameters:
list The array of vertex numbers of the face.
normals The array of normals. Only valid when the polygon mesh has Smooth turned on.
plane_equation The plane equation parameters
uvs The array of UV values

Overridable. Infomation on a polygon mesh face alog with its vertices uvs and face group parameters are passed to the plugin.

UVs values are passed. If the UV values are not needed, use polymesh_face(). If only the parameter's UV values are needed, use polymesh_face_uvuv().

Parameters:
list The array of vertex numbers of the face.
normals The array of normals. Only valid when the polygon mesh has Smooth turned on.

n_uvs The array of UVs values.

virtual void sxsdk::exporter_interface::polymesh_face_uvuv ( int  n_list,
const int  list[],
const sxsdk::vec3 *  normals,
const sxsdk::vec4 *  plane_equation,
const sxsdk::vec4 *  uvs,
void *  aux = 0 
) [inline, virtual]

Overridable. Infomation on a polygon mesh face alog with its vertices uv parameters are passed to the plugin.

The parameters and distance correction UV values are passed. If the UV values are not needed, use polymesh_face(). If only the parameter's UV values are needed, use polymesh_face_uvuv().

Parameters:
list The array of vertex numbers of the face.
normals The array of normals. Only valid when the polygon mesh has Smooth turned on.
plane_equation The plane equation parameters.
uvs The array of parameter UV values and distance correction UV values. In sxsdk::vec4 with 4 values, values 1 and 2 are parameter UV, and values 3 and 4 are distance correction UV values.
